## Hello!

Welcome! If you see this your insanely simple (and **dangerous**) dockerized flask-onnx wrapper for an example classifier is probably running. 

Post JSON to /api/classify in the format:

    {"data": "base64_string" }
and you will get back results:

    {
	    "result": [
		    0.0,
		    0.0,
		    0.0,
		    8.607723510543571e-16,
		    2.4869624556107196e-19,
		    3.6599193994009065e-27,
		    7.588453480689467e-20,
		    0.0,
		    1.0
	    ],
	    "time": 0.008291482925415039
    }
Where result is a ordered list of scores per class (class 0, class 1, etc.)

## Example cURL

    curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"data": ""}' localhost:8080/api/classify
